{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Scope"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"ParentState","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ParentAction","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Child","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":"> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Child","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Reducer","preciseIdentifier":"s:22ComposableArchitecture7ReducerP","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" allows you to transform a parent domain into a child domain, and then run a child"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reduce on that subset domain. This is an important tool for breaking down large features into"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"smaller units and then piecing them together. The smaller units can be easier to understand and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"test, and can even be packaged into their own isolated modules."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You hand ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope"},{"text":" 3 pieces of data for it to do its job:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A writable key path that identifies the child state inside the parent state."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A case path that identifies the child actions inside the parent actions."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A @"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ReducerBuilder"},{"type":"text","text":" closure that describes the reducer you want to run on the child domain."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When run, it will intercept all child actions sent and feed them to the child reducer so that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it can update the parent state and execute effects."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, given the basic scaffolding of child reducer:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct Child {","  struct State {","    \/\/ ...","  }","  enum Action {","    \/\/ ...","  }","  \/\/ ...","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A parent reducer with a domain that holds onto the child domain can use","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/init(state:action:child:)-88vdx","type":"reference"},{"text":" to embed the child reducer in its","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/body-20w8t","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Reducer","struct Parent {","  struct State {","    var child: Child.State","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  enum Action {","    case child(Child.Action)","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  var body: some Reducer<State, Action> {","    Scope(state: \\.child, action: \\.child) {","      Child()","    }","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Additional parent logic and behavior","    }","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Enum state","anchor":"Enum-state","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" reducer also works when state is modeled as an enum, not just a struct. In that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"case you can use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/init(state:action:child:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-9g44g","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" to specify a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"case path that identifies the case of state you want to scope to."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, if your state was modeled as an enum for unloaded\/loading\/loaded, you could"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"scope to the loaded case to run a reduce on only that case:"}]},{"code":["@Reducer","struct Feature {","  enum State {","    case unloaded","    case loading","    case loaded(Child.State)","  }","  enum Action {","    case child(Child.Action)","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  var body: some Reducer<State, Action> {","    Scope(state: \\.loaded, action: \\.child) {","      Child()","    }","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Additional feature logic and behavior","    }","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is important to note that the order of combine ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and your additional feature logic"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"matters. It must be combined before the additional logic. In the other order it would be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"possible for the feature to intercept a child action, switch the state to another case, and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then the scoped child reducer would not be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"bugs, and so we show a runtime warning in that case, and cause test failures.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For an alternative to using ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope"},{"type":"text","text":" with state case paths that enforces the order, check out"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/ifCaseLet(_:action:then:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-rdrb","isActive":true},{"text":" operator.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Embeds a child reducer in a parent domain."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"anchor":"Struct-state","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/init(state:action:child:)-88vdx"],"title":"Struct state"},{"title":"Enum state","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Scope\/init(state:action:child:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-9g44g"],"anchor":"Enum-state"},{"title":"Deprecations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ScopeDeprecations"],"anchor":"Deprecations"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/